race.comment: Hard to rule any of these out. HAPPY BELLIE (4) went back from a wide draw then went through her gears impressively to get up for second last start over 1100m at the Kensington circuit. Fitter for two runs back from a spell and she is desperate for this sort of trip now. Will be tough to hold out. MONTE KATE (1) ran a much better race last time out when second-up from a break, racing handy then battling on well for second over this trip at the Kenso. The handicapper hasn't missed her but her record at or around this distance is outstanding. RINGAROSA (3) chimed in late to grab second when fresh from a spell over this course and distance recently. Second-up form isn't great but from the ideal draw she should be prominent. BEREZKA (2) was just fair when resuming at Warwick Farm last start but she is capable of far better. O'INVINCIBLE (6) can improve this evening at the third run back over a bit more ground and with the blinkers applied.
